1
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:07,880
Can we be friends?

2
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:11,440
<i>Whatever we started together here,</i>

3
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,600
<i>let's end it well here today.</i>

4
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,480
<i>When I was dating Pie,</i>

5
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:19,880
you told me she'd never
had a boyfriend before,

6
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,160
right?

7
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,480
That's right.

8
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,400
She's never had a boyfriend before.

9
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,880
Her first and only boyfriend is you.

10
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:33,360
Everyone says Pie never had a boyfriend.
I want to know who this guy is.

11
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,600
If she still won't tell me
what's in her heart,

12
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,680
what she's hiding from me,

13
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:40,720
I'll find out the truth myself.

14
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,960
I've never seen this side of Pie before.

15
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,800
I can't even picture her
doing anything this adventurous.

16
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:53,880
Maybe…

17
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:57,400
I never really knew her at all.

18
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:29,200
PIE

19
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:56,160
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed</i>
<i>cannot be connected…</i>

20
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:08,880
As for Pun, I want you
to give him another chance.

21
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:11,920
I've already talked to him,
and he'll be here later today.

22
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,640
Puk and I are going to the supermarket
and will be back in the evening.

23
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:18,560
That way, you and Pun
can talk things out calmly.

24
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,079
Will you stop me

25
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,360
if I want to tell the truth?

26
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,560
I won't stop you.

27
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:29,760
Do whatever you think is right.

28
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:34,280
But I want you to really think it through.

29
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,880
Make sure you're certain about it.

30
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:39,160
Think about what could happen,
how things might turn out.

31
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,280
You and I

32
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:45,520
might end up looking like people
who are dishonest and deceitful,

33
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:48,520
using Pun for our own benefit,
just like his mom thinks.

34
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:53,000
Pun will be hurt
for trusting the wrong people all along.

35
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:57,080
It won't just be you and me
disappointing him,

36
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:58,920
but also Win.

37
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,480
If we think about it ideally,

38
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,400
if he knew the truth,

39
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,160
he might be able to accept

40
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:10,880
that you had a boyfriend
and had a miscarriage.

41
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:16,440
But if he finds out
that Win, his closest brother,

42
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:19,640
was part of the deception,
hiding the truth all along,

43
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:22,480
no matter how idealistic it seems,

44
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,080
he won't be able to accept it.

45
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,760
Being deceived by strangers

46
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:34,320
doesn't hurt as much as being betrayed
by someone close to you.

47
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:43,560
Pie.

48
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:48,640
Right now, your words

49
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:51,000
could either solve the problem

50
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,520
or create even more problems for everyone.

51
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:56,240
I want you to think

52
00:05:56,320 --> 00:06:00,640
very carefully before you speak, okay?

53
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:33,000
PIE

54
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,840
Hello. Who are you looking for?

55
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,280
What are you doing here?!

56
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:58,760
Leave right now! You're not welcome here.

57
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:00,720
I know.

58
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,360
But I need to talk to Pie
about something important.

59
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,560
No, you're not talking to her.
Just go back.

60
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:06,160
Ma'am, calm down.

61
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,880
Don't you understand what I'm saying?

62
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,440
I said go! Puk!

63
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,200
Get rid of him!
Why are you just standing there?

64
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:12,800
He's too big, I can't get rid of him.

65
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:14,800
Even if you can't, you have to.
Get him out!

66
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,280
- Hey!
- Get out!

67
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,320
Ma'am!

68
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,480
- You can't come in.
- Are you not listening?

69
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,200
I said go!

70
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:25,760
I know you don't want me to see Pie.

71
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:29,200
But I really need to talk to her.
I'm sorry.

72
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:31,240
- I told you no! Puk!
- Sir, you can't come in!

73
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,560
- Get him out right now!
- Sir!

74
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:35,240
Get out! I said go!

75
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:36,560
- Pie!
- Hey!

76
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,080
- Come out and talk.
- Don't call my daughter's name!

77
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,280
- I won't allow it.
- Win?

78
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,480
Do you understand?

79
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,960
If you don't leave, I'll call the police.

80
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:45,160
Win!

81
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,440
Why are you here?

82
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:52,000
No! You're not talking to her!

83
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:54,720
What's so important
that you have to talk to her?

84
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:57,120
Pie, don't listen to him.

85
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,360
He's trying to deceive you.

86
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:01,000
He's tricked you before,
he can do it again.

87
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:04,160
Pie, people can change,

88
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:06,560
but their true nature is hard to change.

89
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,920
I've never deceived Pie.

90
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,440
Alright,

91
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:12,280
there are things I said
that didn't match my true feelings,

92
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,320
but that's because you asked me to.

93
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,480
Do you want me to tell you
what it was about?

94
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,640
Shut up.

95
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:17,800
Say it.

96
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,520
Pie.

97
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,240
- That day--
- Pie!

98
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:29,680
Don't listen to him.

99
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,520
It's not important.

100
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:35,720
Right now, the most important thing
for you is Pun.

101
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:38,080
He'll be here this evening.

102
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:40,480
You need to get ready, alright?

103
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:42,880
We need to talk before you get ready,
or it'll be too late.

104
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,720
What's too late?

105
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:47,680
Just say it. What's too late? Say it!

106
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,600
Pun saw the picture of us together.

107
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,880
You together?

108
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,560
Be quiet, Puk.

109
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:55,800
I need to talk to Win alone.
I'll handle it.

110
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:57,200
No, Pie.

111
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:59,800
I won't let you be alone with him.
Do it here.

112
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:04,800
Mom, if you don't go,
I'll go with Win myself.

113
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,520
- Pie!
- Win, come here.

114
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,760
- No! Stop!
- Mom!

115
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:10,800
I'm not letting you go. We'll talk here.

116
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:13,960
I've arranged a meeting with Pun.
What if he comes and you're not here?

117
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:16,000
If you want me to meet him,

118
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,320
you have to let me talk to Win alone.

119
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:24,880
You've always told me what to do,

120
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:28,240
and I've always listened,
which is why my life turned out like this.

121
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:30,000
But not today, Mom.

122
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,560
You have two choices.

123
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:42,080
If you want me to meet Pun,
you have to leave.

124
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,520
But if you don't leave,

125
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,400
I'll go myself.

126
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,200
Pie.

127
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:55,280
If you can't decide,
we'll just argue like this,

128
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,680
waiting for Pun to come.

129
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,520
Fine!

130
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:09,160
I'll give you 15 minutes.

131
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,360
If I call and you still haven't left,

132
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,960
I'll come back and drag you
out of this house myself.

133
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,000
Puk, let's go.

134
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,320
Yes, ma'am.

135
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,240
What picture are you talking about
that Pun saw?

136
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,840
The toboggan ride picture. Remember?

137
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:56,960
The one taken on the ride.

138
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:59,080
You were blocking me completely
in the picture.

139
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,360
You were laughing, teasing me,
and asked to keep the picture.

140
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,520
Remember?

141
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,840
Win, you got blocked. Look!

142
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:09,120
Want to go again?

143
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:12,720
Pie.

144
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,600
This is Koh's car.

145
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:29,000
Pun said you kept the picture in the book.

146
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:44,400
KOH

147
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,360
Pie.

148
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,200
Pie.

149
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,440
Found it!

150
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,280
Pun still doesn't know
that I'm the guy in the picture.

151
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,960
He asked, but I didn't tell him.

152
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:45,960
It's too late now, Pie.
He has already seen the picture.

153
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,960
Tell me, Pie.

154
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:53,280
All this time,
why didn't you tell him about…

155
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,000
About us?

156
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:07,960
I didn't want to talk about it.

157
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:10,560
I didn't want to tell anyone.

158
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:12,520
But don't you think
you have to tell him now?

159
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:16,640
If you don't, he will find out somehow.

160
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:18,600
Even if he doesn't investigate,

161
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:20,840
I was already planning to tell him.

162
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:23,560
I don't want to hide anything anymore.
I've had enough.

163
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,160
Staying like this isn't making me happy.

164
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:29,320
I'm going to tell him everything,
all of it.

165
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,680
If Pun can't accept it…

166
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:36,240
then I'm ready to divorce.

167
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,960
<i>This is my friend.</i>

168
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:12,880
He's your friend, not mine.

169
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,240
I think she has someone else.

170
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:18,800
No way.

171
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:20,120
How do you know?

172
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,560
Just a guess.

173
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:23,000
Do you know this place?

174
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:24,680
It's hard to tell.

175
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:26,760
Plenty of places have rides like this.

176
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:28,120
Have you ever been on one?

177
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,640
I guess I have.

178
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,200
Who did you go with?

179
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:32,960
By myself.

180
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,360
<i>Pun still doesn't know</i>
<i>that I'm the guy in the picture.</i>

181
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,720
<i>He asked, but I didn't tell him.</i>

182
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,400
Pie.

183
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,480
I'm sorry for coming into your life

184
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:29,440
and making you face these troubles.

185
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:32,880
If we hadn't met,

186
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,120
if I hadn't known Pun,

187
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:41,760
you wouldn't have had to deal
with this awkward situation.

188
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,360
Forget it.

189
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:56,440
It already happened.

190
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,600
And back then…

191
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,960
no one knew what the future would be.

192
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:12,680
I'm at fault

193
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:17,400
for not telling Pun the truth
before we got married.

194
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,520
Tell me honestly, Pie.

195
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,000
Did you not tell him…

196
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,160
because of your mom?

197
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,640
I don't want to blame anyone else.

198
00:19:23,360 --> 00:19:24,360
Let's just say…

199
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,040
I was wrong.

200
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:32,000
And now I'm ready
to take responsibility for everything,

201
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:35,480
no matter what happens.

202
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:02,440
Once you talk to Pun,

203
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:05,800
let me know, alright?

204
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:31,360
What the hell is this?

205
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:27,920
<i>So you've never brought a guy before?</i>

206
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,320
That's true.

207
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:31,120
I must be someone special.

208
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:33,600
You could say that.

209
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:40,680
<i>That's why you're so sweet.</i>

210
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,320
<i>Quick to forget</i>

211
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:46,280
and easygoing. I like that about you.

212
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:49,880
I know you trust me.

213
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,840
You're easygoing.

214
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,640
You'll be fine with everything.

215
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:56,360
You're the sweetest.

216
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:27,680
MOM

217
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:30,000
- Yes, Mom.
- <i>Pie.</i>

218
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:32,840
Has Win left yet?
Pun is about to go see you.

219
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,920
- He's gone.
- <i>Good.</i>

220
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:38,560
Get yourself together
and talk things through calmly.

221
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:41,360
Everything depends on what you say.

222
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,640
Yes.

223
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:53,920
I'm sorry, Mom.

224
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:14,360
I've come to take you home.

225
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:21,560
Pun.

226
00:25:23,440 --> 00:25:24,400
Before we go,

227
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:27,920
I need to talk
and clear things up with you first.

228
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,200
Of course.

229
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:32,960
Shall we…

230
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:35,360
go home and talk?

231
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:36,280
No.

232
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:39,320
I want to talk here.

233
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:42,280
After you hear me out,

234
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:45,520
you might not want me
to come home with you.

235
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:50,640
Well.

236
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,240
Just tell me then.

237
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:58,480
I'm listening.

238
00:26:22,760 --> 00:26:24,160
You once told me

239
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:27,040
that you liked me

240
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:31,160
because I'm someone you can trust,

241
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:34,880
someone uncomplicated.

242
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:39,960
But the truth is…

243
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,680
I'm not a good person.

244
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:50,200
I've been hiding things from you,

245
00:26:51,760 --> 00:26:53,080
things I never shared.

246
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:00,440
Before we got together,

247
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:04,800
I had a relationship with a guy.

248
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:16,880
That guy is…

249
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:24,200
Win.

250
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:37,920
Win?

251
00:27:41,200 --> 00:27:42,440
Koh?

252
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:44,760
Yes.

253
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:49,520
We were together

254
00:27:50,360 --> 00:27:52,920
when I went to Mae Hong Son
for my final project.

255
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:57,080
I never told you

256
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:00,760
because I didn't want to think about it.

257
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,640
And I didn't think

258
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:07,640
you and he would know each other.

259
00:28:11,840 --> 00:28:13,040
So, when we met…

260
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:18,120
and you found out I knew Win,

261
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,960
why didn't you tell me the truth?

262
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:28,000
<i>Have you thought about how I'll be?</i>

263
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:30,640
Pie, everything I have today
is because of Pun.

264
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:32,520
What if you tell him,

265
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:35,040
and he wants the truth, then finds out

266
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,800
you were pregnant
before finishing university?

267
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:39,800
What will you do if he gets upset
and asks for a divorce?

268
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:43,160
Telling the truth
might make everything worse.

269
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:52,880
I'm…

270
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:58,840
I'm scared you'll be angry with me.

271
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:02,960
You're scared I'll be angry,
but not that I'll be hurt?

272
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:24,720
Alright then.

273
00:29:28,280 --> 00:29:30,040
I'll let it go.

274
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:31,120
Okay?

275
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:39,520
Is that everything?

276
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:45,600
There's more.

277
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:47,360
Go ahead and say it.

278
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:50,240
I'm listening.

279
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:03,920
I was pregnant, but I miscarried

280
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:07,200
because of an accident.

281
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:29,280
Pie.

282
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:37,240
You were pregnant…

283
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:42,040
with Win's baby?

284
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:49,680
Yes.

285
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:57,840
Pun.

286
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:01,640
I know having a child is important to you.

287
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:05,640
It's something I feel deeply guilty about.

288
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,160
If you remember,

289
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:13,440
before we argued,
I decided to tell you everything.

290
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:16,120
But you said you were stressed
and not ready to hear it.

291
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:28,920
Today,

292
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:32,840
I've told you the truth about everything.

293
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:36,760
Now, think about it.

294
00:31:38,920 --> 00:31:41,440
Do you still want me
to come home with you?

295
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:32,920
Well…

296
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:38,720
It's a normal thing, Pie.

297
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:43,880
Everyone has a past.

298
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:47,360
Right?

299
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:49,920
About your accident…

300
00:32:51,560 --> 00:32:52,680
I'm sorry.

301
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:10,400
Let's leave it behind…

302
00:33:13,840 --> 00:33:15,160
and start over.

303
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:21,840
Pun.

304
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:25,560
Do you really want that?

305
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:29,760
Yes.

306
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:34,040
Whatever you've done

307
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:38,280
in the past,

308
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:42,680
I can accept all of it.

309
00:33:49,760 --> 00:33:51,760
I don't want to lose you.

310
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:00,280
I won't divorce you.

311
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:05,040
Let's start fresh.

312
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:13,199
I love you, Pie.

313
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:17,320
Okay?

314
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:31,800
Go inside first.

315
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:34,560
I need to handle something.

316
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:37,600
Something?

317
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:38,600
Yes.

318
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:41,240
Something personal I don't want to share,

319
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:44,920
just like you have things
you don't want to share.

320
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:51,080
I hope you understand.

321
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:55,560
Yes.

322
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,640
Huh?

323
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:31,120
You told Pun everything?

324
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:32,280
Yes.

325
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,280
Oh my.

326
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:38,240
What exactly did you tell him?

327
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:39,680
Everything.

328
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:43,120
Including the miscarriage?

329
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:45,360
Yes.

330
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:48,160
Oh, Pie.

331
00:36:48,240 --> 00:36:51,440
What did he say? Is he angry?

332
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:53,240
He's not angry.

333
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:56,040
He said he understands.

334
00:36:56,120 --> 00:36:58,640
Is it really that easy, Pie?

335
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:02,040
I don't know.

336
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:04,840
If he said he's not angry,
then he's not angry.

337
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:07,680
I don't really know why, Mom.

338
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:21,600
I have to go, Mom.

339
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,320
Hello, Mother.

340
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:37,880
Why did you hang up?

341
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:39,920
Why didn't you continue talking?

342
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:43,320
And what you said
about Pun not being angry,

343
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:45,800
did you do something wrong?
Why would he be angry?

344
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:50,160
Mother.

345
00:37:51,080 --> 00:37:53,280
It's a personal matter between me and Pun.

346
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:57,760
I've already told him everything.

347
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:02,200
If you want to know,
you can ask Pun yourself.

348
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:05,040
If he wants you to know,

349
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:07,160
he'll be the one to tell you.

350
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:10,200
Are you saying
I'm being nosy and interfering?

351
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,560
With all due respect, Mother,

352
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:15,160
I never meant to insult you.

353
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:17,720
I'm just speaking the truth.

354
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:19,440
You don't need to try to hide it.

355
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:23,040
I know you must have
something bad to hide.

356
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:24,280
I've had a feeling about it all along.

357
00:38:24,360 --> 00:38:25,360
Yes.

358
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:27,040
I'm not a good person.

359
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:30,040
But I've never claimed to be.

360
00:38:31,520 --> 00:38:35,160
I didn't want to say anything
or cause any problems, so I stayed quiet.

361
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:37,560
Just acting innocent, aren't you?

362
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:41,040
I'm not acting innocent.

363
00:38:41,120 --> 00:38:42,960
And I'm not pretending to be proper.

364
00:38:43,040 --> 00:38:45,160
This is just how I look, Mother.

365
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:51,240
If you want to scold me,
feel free to do so.

366
00:38:51,320 --> 00:38:54,240
If it's true, I'll accept it.

367
00:38:55,280 --> 00:38:56,760
But if it's not true,

368
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:59,520
if that's okay, Mother,

369
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:02,320
I'd like to leave it here.

370
00:39:06,040 --> 00:39:06,960
Sorry.

371
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:13,680
Did you hear that?

372
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:15,320
Did you hear her talk back to me, Tian?

373
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:17,280
Look at her!

374
00:39:17,360 --> 00:39:18,840
Her true colors are showing now.

375
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:20,880
My intuition has never been wrong.

376
00:39:36,520 --> 00:39:39,000
Win, seaweed dim sum.

377
00:39:39,560 --> 00:39:41,800
Also, some pork dumplings.

378
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:44,000
Here, take two pieces.

379
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:45,920
There you go.

380
00:39:46,520 --> 00:39:47,480
Enough already.

381
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:51,560
No need to do that much for him
to know you like him.

382
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:56,880
I mean, like eating dim sum.

383
00:40:13,960 --> 00:40:16,680
<i>Meet me at the gym. I need to vent.</i>

384
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:20,280
Gotta go. Pun's calling me.

385
00:40:21,720 --> 00:40:22,880
Oh?

386
00:40:23,440 --> 00:40:24,680
Rok.

387
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:26,120
Can we talk for a minute?

388
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:32,560
Be right back.

389
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:40,240
Hey.

390
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:41,960
What's up?

391
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:50,800
Sorry for being blunt.

392
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:53,040
I just need to be sure.

393
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:57,720
Do you like me?

394
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,360
You're being so direct.

395
00:41:10,240 --> 00:41:11,560
Why are you asking that?

396
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:17,680
Well…

397
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:19,880
If you do,

398
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:24,880
I'm sorry.

399
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:30,600
I don't feel the same way.

400
00:41:33,520 --> 00:41:34,600
I'm really sorry.

401
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:50,880
If I misunderstood

402
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:53,200
and you didn't feel that way,

403
00:41:54,640 --> 00:41:56,400
I apologize for saying anything.

404
00:41:59,520 --> 00:42:01,280
I just want to stay coworkers like before.

405
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:07,840
Win, you're so blunt.

406
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:10,720
Couldn't you be a bit more subtle?

407
00:42:17,120 --> 00:42:18,360
I'm really sorry, Rok.

408
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:23,800
No need to apologize.

409
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:25,360
You didn't do anything wrong.

410
00:42:27,040 --> 00:42:29,000
Thanks for being upfront with me.

411
00:42:31,440 --> 00:42:32,680
I'm going to go now.

412
00:43:05,440 --> 00:43:06,440
She's back.

413
00:43:38,560 --> 00:43:39,520
Huh?

414
00:43:40,920 --> 00:43:43,240
What did you say? Pun's not angry?

415
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:45,800
Yes.

416
00:43:45,880 --> 00:43:47,080
He's okay with it.

417
00:43:47,960 --> 00:43:49,200
We're starting over.

418
00:43:50,520 --> 00:43:51,880
Starting over?

419
00:43:53,480 --> 00:43:55,400
Does he really feel that way?

420
00:43:57,200 --> 00:43:59,400
<i>He cleared things with you,</i>
<i>now it's my turn.</i>

421
00:43:59,480 --> 00:44:00,760
<i>He wants to see me.</i>

422
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:05,680
Well, good.

423
00:44:06,960 --> 00:44:08,760
This way, we can talk honestly.

424
00:44:31,520 --> 00:44:32,400
How's it going?

425
00:44:37,240 --> 00:44:39,240
Put on your gloves and meet me in there.

426
00:45:50,200 --> 00:45:51,160
Hey.

427
00:45:53,880 --> 00:45:54,760
Did you really bleed?

428
00:45:56,320 --> 00:45:57,360
Hey.

429
00:45:57,440 --> 00:45:58,440
Sorry.

430
00:45:58,520 --> 00:45:59,680
I didn't see that.

431
00:46:00,840 --> 00:46:01,880
It's okay.

432
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:05,360
Hey.

433
00:46:09,280 --> 00:46:10,200
Let me see.

434
00:46:19,440 --> 00:46:20,560
Are you satisfied now?

435
00:46:22,480 --> 00:46:23,480
Not yet.

436
00:46:24,040 --> 00:46:25,600
What do you want to do?

437
00:46:26,280 --> 00:46:28,880
Want to keep hitting me
until you feel better?

438
00:46:29,680 --> 00:46:31,960
Then we can talk without any violence.

439
00:46:38,080 --> 00:46:39,040
Take a shower.

440
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:41,320
Then we'll talk.

441
00:47:08,480 --> 00:47:09,480
Hey.

442
00:47:10,840 --> 00:47:12,040
Hey.

443
00:47:14,920 --> 00:47:16,160
What are you thinking?

444
00:47:16,760 --> 00:47:17,920
Sit down.

445
00:47:39,120 --> 00:47:40,200
That stings.

446
00:47:42,680 --> 00:47:43,680
Sorry.

447
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:47,040
I forgot about your fresh wound.

448
00:47:55,520 --> 00:47:56,760
Let's do it again.

449
00:47:57,280 --> 00:47:58,360
Come on.

450
00:47:59,160 --> 00:48:00,200
I'll do it myself.

451
00:48:15,160 --> 00:48:16,840
You know about me and Pie, right?

452
00:48:20,920 --> 00:48:22,080
Hey.

453
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:23,600
I just talked to my wife.

454
00:48:24,640 --> 00:48:26,320
And now you know too.

455
00:48:28,480 --> 00:48:29,840
The news spreads fast, huh?

456
00:48:31,600 --> 00:48:32,520
Pun.

457
00:48:34,640 --> 00:48:36,240
I'm sorry.

458
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:37,520
I didn't think it would be a big deal.

459
00:48:37,600 --> 00:48:39,160
Do you think it's a small thing?

460
00:48:39,240 --> 00:48:40,960
It's not a small thing.

461
00:48:41,760 --> 00:48:44,600
But I didn't think it was important.

462
00:48:44,680 --> 00:48:46,640
You and Pie seem happy together already.

463
00:48:46,720 --> 00:48:48,520
This isn't about me and Pie.

464
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:51,080
It's about you and me.

465
00:48:52,480 --> 00:48:54,120
If you still see me as your brother,

466
00:48:55,880 --> 00:48:58,120
you should've told me the truth.

467
00:48:58,200 --> 00:49:00,120
I thought Pie didn't tell you.

468
00:49:00,200 --> 00:49:02,400
I didn't want to cause trouble
between you and her.

469
00:49:04,200 --> 00:49:05,920
You didn't want to cause trouble,

470
00:49:07,080 --> 00:49:08,640
so you helped her lie?

471
00:49:10,560 --> 00:49:12,320
How does that solve anything?

472
00:49:23,600 --> 00:49:24,920
Pie said you were okay.

473
00:49:27,280 --> 00:49:28,920
But deep down, you weren't, right?

474
00:49:35,600 --> 00:49:37,640
I'm the one
who's been looking out for you,

475
00:49:39,000 --> 00:49:40,480
having your back.

476
00:49:41,800 --> 00:49:43,600
But when it comes to me,

477
00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:45,760
you choose to help

478
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:47,880
and protect others.

479
00:49:54,280 --> 00:49:55,600
Why are you helping

480
00:49:57,160 --> 00:49:58,360
and protecting her?

481
00:50:04,840 --> 00:50:06,440
You still love Pie, don't you?

482
00:50:24,880 --> 00:50:27,040
Me and Pie can't go back
to how we were anymore.

483
00:50:37,120 --> 00:50:38,040
Well.

484
00:50:39,360 --> 00:50:41,280
Hearing that makes me feel a bit better.

485
00:50:53,240 --> 00:50:55,440
What's in the past, let it go.

486
00:50:57,320 --> 00:50:58,520
We just have to…

487
00:50:59,880 --> 00:51:01,120
brace ourselves

488
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:04,400
for what's coming next.

489
00:52:30,880 --> 00:52:32,160
Where are you going, Pun?

490
00:52:34,280 --> 00:52:35,560
I'm going to sleep at Mom's.

491
00:52:36,840 --> 00:52:38,120
Is something wrong?

492
00:52:38,800 --> 00:52:39,840
I can't sleep.

493
00:52:42,640 --> 00:52:44,640
I guess it's because you left
and went to your mom's.

494
00:52:45,800 --> 00:52:47,440
So I got used to sleeping alone.

495
00:52:48,760 --> 00:52:51,080
Now that someone else is here,
I can't sleep.

496
00:52:51,880 --> 00:52:53,240
I'm someone else?

497
00:52:53,320 --> 00:52:55,680
I don't want to talk
about who you are right now.

498
00:52:58,200 --> 00:52:59,680
Because I'm starting to wonder

499
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:02,120
who you really are.

500
00:53:50,160 --> 00:53:51,360
What are you doing?

501
00:53:54,920 --> 00:53:56,240
I'm going to release the spider.

502
00:53:56,320 --> 00:53:58,560
The workers will step on it
when they come to work.

503
00:53:59,920 --> 00:54:01,080
No need.

504
00:54:02,800 --> 00:54:04,200
Leave it there.

505
00:54:13,160 --> 00:54:14,200
It's a punishment

506
00:54:15,640 --> 00:54:17,440
for coming into the house
and making it dirty.

507
00:54:21,440 --> 00:54:23,360
If it makes a mistake
and gets let off easily,

508
00:54:24,840 --> 00:54:26,400
it seems like it hasn't paid
for its actions.

509
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:41,040
Let it stay locked up for a while.

510
00:54:43,120 --> 00:54:44,720
When I'm ready,

511
00:54:48,000 --> 00:54:49,080
I'll let it go.

512
00:55:05,440 --> 00:55:06,800
Hello.

513
00:55:06,880 --> 00:55:09,560
Hi, everyone.

514
00:55:09,640 --> 00:55:11,760
Where is everyone?

515
00:55:21,200 --> 00:55:22,040
Hello, Uncle Dech.

516
00:55:22,120 --> 00:55:23,040
Hello.

517
00:55:23,560 --> 00:55:24,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

518
00:55:25,920 --> 00:55:28,000
Where have you two been getting cozy?

519
00:55:28,080 --> 00:55:29,720
I came up and couldn't find anyone.

520
00:55:30,560 --> 00:55:33,040
We were looking at some work inside.

521
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:39,440
Once you could get Pie to forgive you,
you disappear, huh?

522
00:55:39,520 --> 00:55:43,240
You used to call me every night,
but now it's quiet.

523
00:55:50,440 --> 00:55:54,520
So, my trick
to get Pie back worked, right?

524
00:55:55,760 --> 00:55:57,040
You should ask her that.

525
00:55:59,160 --> 00:56:01,960
Did you like the surprise
I did for you at home?

526
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:02,880
Hey.

527
00:56:03,560 --> 00:56:05,040
It was all Mink's idea.

528
00:56:07,560 --> 00:56:08,840
She must have liked it.

529
00:56:08,920 --> 00:56:10,800
Otherwise, you wouldn't
have come back and made up.

530
00:56:11,920 --> 00:56:13,240
You should thank me, Pie.

531
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:16,600
If you fight again, feel free to call me.

532
00:56:16,680 --> 00:56:18,640
I have plenty more tricks to share.

533
00:56:19,240 --> 00:56:20,640
I think we won't need that, Mink.

534
00:56:21,800 --> 00:56:24,240
Pie and I have worked things out.

535
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:27,680
We probably won't fight again.

536
00:56:42,480 --> 00:56:46,920
Everyone, I need coffee.
Let's wrap up the work talk quickly.

537
00:56:47,000 --> 00:56:48,720
So I can get some coffee.

538
00:56:48,800 --> 00:56:50,280
Pie, let's catch up on work.

539
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:51,200
Okay.

540
00:56:51,280 --> 00:56:54,920
Uncle Dech, feel free
to update Pie on the work.

541
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:58,240
I'll take Mink to check out the connection
between the cafe and the museum.

542
00:56:58,320 --> 00:56:59,040
Alright.

543
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:01,600
I have a new idea to present.

544
00:57:02,440 --> 00:57:03,920
You can discuss it with the architect.

545
00:57:04,000 --> 00:57:05,760
Sounds good. Let's go.

546
00:57:05,840 --> 00:57:06,960
Let's go.

547
00:57:13,640 --> 00:57:17,000
Pun, the photoshoot we did together,
everyone loved it!

548
00:57:17,080 --> 00:57:19,480
- Really?
- Yes, really!

549
00:57:22,440 --> 00:57:24,200
- Pie.
- Yes?

550
00:57:24,280 --> 00:57:26,240
I apologize on Mink's behalf.

551
00:57:26,320 --> 00:57:28,560
I probably spoiled her a bit,

552
00:57:28,640 --> 00:57:31,840
and now,
she's being careless with the situation.

553
00:57:31,920 --> 00:57:33,600
It's okay, Uncle Dech.

554
00:57:35,240 --> 00:57:37,200
Let's update on the work now.

555
00:57:37,280 --> 00:57:38,720
- Let's go.
- After you.

556
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:44,320
The person I used to date is Win.

557
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:46,600
You've said everything,
so you must feel relieved.

558
00:57:46,680 --> 00:57:48,840
<i>But for me, now that I know the truth,</i>

559
00:57:48,920 --> 00:57:50,680
<i>I'm really hurt.</i>

560
00:57:50,760 --> 00:57:54,480
If you're going to say one thing
and do another to get back at me…

561
00:57:55,960 --> 00:57:57,960
If it makes you feel better, go ahead.

562
00:57:58,040 --> 00:57:59,440
<i>By the time everything is over,</i>

563
00:58:00,560 --> 00:58:02,160
<i>I'll feel less guilty.</i>

564
00:58:02,880 --> 00:58:04,920
No husband, no friends.

565
00:58:05,560 --> 00:58:07,960
Now everyone knows
what you're really like.

566
00:58:10,960 --> 00:58:11,960
Yeah.

567
00:58:12,040 --> 00:58:13,440
If you hurt Pie,

568
00:58:13,520 --> 00:58:15,080
I won't just stand by and do nothing.

569
00:58:18,520 --> 00:58:20,240
CERTIFICATE OF MARRIAGE

570
00:58:47,000 --> 00:58:51,080
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
